    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Bluestocking Blues</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Julie Crosby letter opposes Judith Shulevitz's September 10 letter on Hillary Rodham Clinton (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>I am often dumbfounded that intelligent women can begin a conversation by lamenting the lack of female representatives in government and then conclude it with a catty comment about Hillary's hair, home or husband that serves to dismiss her. It is distressing that this treatment of powerful women hasn't changed in over 100 years, as Shulevitz demonstrates in her comparison of Hillary to the bluestocking, Henrietta Stackpole.</p>
        <p>Julie Crosby  New York</p>
      </block>
